Note:
Runa Standard Library: Comprehensive CSV Module Tests

This test suite validates all CSV module functionality including reading, writing,
streaming, dialect detection, schema validation, error handling, and performance
characteristics. Provides comprehensive coverage of edge cases and production scenarios.

Tests cover all three CSV modules:
- csv/csv.runa: Core types and utilities
- csv/reader.runa: Reading and parsing functionality  
- csv/writer.runa: Writing and formatting functionality

Includes performance benchmarks, memory usage validation, and cross-platform
compatibility tests for production readiness verification.
:End Note

Import "csv/csv" as csv_core
Import "csv/reader" as csv_reader
Import "csv/writer" as csv_writer
Import "testing" as testing
Import "io/file" as file_io

Note: Test Result Types

Type CSVTestResult is Dictionary with:
    test_name as String
    passed as Boolean
    error_message as Optional[String]
    execution_time_ms as Integer
    details as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type CSVTestSuite is Dictionary with:
    suite_name as String
    total_tests as Integer
    passed_tests as Integer
    failed_tests as Integer
    results as List[CSVTestResult]
    execution_time_ms as Integer

Note: Main Test Execution

Process called "run_all_csv_tests" returns CSVTestSuite:
    Note: Execute comprehensive CSV test suite
    Try:
        Let start_time be get_current_time_ms
        Let all_results be empty list
        
        Note: Test each CSV module component
        Let core_results be test_csv_core_functionality
        Let reader_results be test_csv_reader_functionality
        Let writer_results be test_csv_writer_functionality
        Let integration_results be test_csv_integration_scenarios
        Let performance_results be test_csv_performance_characteristics
        Let error_handling_results be test_csv_error_handling
        
        Note: Combine all test results
        Set all_results to concatenate_test_results with results_lists as list containing:
            core_results, reader_results, writer_results, integration_results, 
            performance_results, error_handling_results
        
        Let end_time be get_current_time_ms
        Let execution_time be end_time minus start_time
        
        Let passed_count be count_passed_tests with results as all_results
        Let failed_count be (length of all_results) minus passed_count
        
        Return CSVTestSuite with:
            suite_name as "Runa CSV Module Comprehensive Tests"
            total_tests as length of all_results
            passed_tests as passed_count
            failed_tests as failed_count
            results as all_results
            execution_time_ms as execution_time
    
    Catch error:
        Return CSVTestSuite with:
            suite_name as "CSV Test Suite (Failed)"
            total_tests as 0
            passed_tests as 0
            failed_tests as 1
            results as list containing create_error_test_result with error_msg as error as String
            execution_time_ms as 0

Note: Core CSV Functionality Tests

Process called "test_csv_core_functionality" returns List[CSVTestResult]:
    Note: Test core CSV types, dialects, and basic operations
    Let results be empty list
    
    Note: Test CSV dialect creation and configuration
    Let test_start be get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let default_dialect be csv_core.create_default_csv_dialect
        If default_dialect.delimiter is equal to "," and default_dialect.quotechar is equal to "\"":
            Add create_test_result with name as "CSV Dialect Creation" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
        Else:
            Add create_test_result with name as "CSV Dialect Creation" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Invalid default dialect properties" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "CSV Dialect Creation" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Note: Test CSV line parsing with standard format
    Set test_start to get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let test_line be "\"John Doe\",25,\"New York, NY\",true"
        Let dialect be csv_core.create_default_csv_dialect
        Let parse_result be csv_core.parse_csv_line with line as test_line and dialect as dialect
        
        Match parse_result:
            When csv_core.ParseSuccess with fields as parsed_fields:
                If length of parsed_fields is equal to 4 and 
                   parsed_fields at index 0 is equal to "John Doe" and
                   parsed_fields at index 1 is equal to "25" and
                   parsed_fields at index 2 is equal to "New York, NY" and
                   parsed_fields at index 3 is equal to "true":
                    Add create_test_result with name as "CSV Line Parsing" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
                Else:
                    Add create_test_result with name as "CSV Line Parsing" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Incorrect field parsing" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
            
            When csv_core.ParseFailure with error_msg as parse_error:
                Add create_test_result with name as "CSV Line Parsing" and passed as false and error as Some with value as parse_error and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "CSV Line Parsing" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Note: Test CSV line generation
    Set test_start to get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let test_fields be list containing "Alice", "30", "San Francisco", "false"
        Let dialect be csv_core.create_default_csv_dialect
        Let generated_line be csv_core.generate_csv_line with fields as test_fields and dialect as dialect
        
        Let expected_line be "Alice,30,San Francisco,false"
        If generated_line is equal to expected_line:
            Add create_test_result with name as "CSV Line Generation" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
        Else:
            Add create_test_result with name as "CSV Line Generation" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Generated line doesn't match expected: " plus generated_line and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "CSV Line Generation" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Note: Test CSV row creation and field access
    Set test_start to get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let test_fields be list containing "Bob", "35", "Chicago"
        Let headers be list containing "name", "age", "city"
        Let csv_row be csv_core.create_csv_row with fields as test_fields and headers as headers and line_num as 2
        
        If csv_row contains key "name" and csv_row["name"] is equal to "Bob" and
           csv_row contains key "age" and csv_row["age"] is equal to "35" and
           csv_row contains key "city" and csv_row["city"] is equal to "Chicago":
            Add create_test_result with name as "CSV Row Creation" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
        Else:
            Add create_test_result with name as "CSV Row Creation" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "CSV row field access failed" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "CSV Row Creation" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Note: Test field quoting necessity detection
    Set test_start to get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let dialect be csv_core.create_default_csv_dialect
        
        Let needs_quotes_comma be csv_core.field_needs_quoting with field as "Hello, World" and dialect as dialect
        Let needs_quotes_quote be csv_core.field_needs_quoting with field as "Say \"Hello\"" and dialect as dialect
        Let needs_quotes_newline be csv_core.field_needs_quoting with field as "Line1\nLine2" and dialect as dialect
        Let needs_quotes_simple be csv_core.field_needs_quoting with field as "SimpleText" and dialect as dialect
        
        If needs_quotes_comma and needs_quotes_quote and needs_quotes_newline and not needs_quotes_simple:
            Add create_test_result with name as "Field Quoting Detection" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
        Else:
            Add create_test_result with name as "Field Quoting Detection" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Incorrect quoting necessity detection" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "Field Quoting Detection" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Note: Test escape character handling
    Set test_start to get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let field_with_quotes be "She said \"Hello\" to me"
        Let dialect be csv_core.create_default_csv_dialect
        Let escaped_field be csv_core.escape_field_content with field as field_with_quotes and dialect as dialect
        
        Let expected_escaped be "She said \"\"Hello\"\" to me"
        If escaped_field is equal to expected_escaped:
            Add create_test_result with name as "Field Escaping" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
        Else:
            Add create_test_result with name as "Field Escaping" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Incorrect field escaping: " plus escaped_field and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "Field Escaping" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Return results

Note: CSV Reader Functionality Tests

Process called "test_csv_reader_functionality" returns List[CSVTestResult]:
    Note: Test CSV reading, streaming, and parsing capabilities
    Let results be empty list
    
    Note: Test basic CSV string parsing
    Let test_start be get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let csv_content be "name,age,city\nAlice,25,Boston\nBob,30,Seattle\nCharlie,35,Denver"
        Let options be csv_core.create_csv_reader_options
        Set options.has_header to true
        
        Let parse_result be csv_core.parse_csv_string with csv_string as csv_content and options as options
        Match parse_result:
            When csv_core.CSVSuccess with rows as parsed_rows and row_count as count and has_header as has_hdr:
                If count is equal to 3 and has_hdr and length of parsed_rows is equal to 3:
                    Let first_row be parsed_rows at index 0
                    If first_row contains key "name" and first_row["name"] is equal to "Alice" and
                       first_row contains key "age" and first_row["age"] is equal to "25" and
                       first_row contains key "city" and first_row["city"] is equal to "Boston":
                        Add create_test_result with name as "CSV String Parsing" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
                    Else:
                        Add create_test_result with name as "CSV String Parsing" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Incorrect row data parsing" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
                Else:
                    Add create_test_result with name as "CSV String Parsing" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Incorrect parsing result counts" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
            
            When csv_core.CSVFailure with error as parse_error:
                Add create_test_result with name as "CSV String Parsing" and passed as false and error as Some with value as parse_error.message and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "CSV String Parsing" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Note: Test dialect detection capabilities
    Set test_start to get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let semicolon_csv be "name;age;city\nAlice;25;Boston\nBob;30;Seattle"
        Let detected_dialect be csv_core.detect_csv_dialect with sample as semicolon_csv
        
        If detected_dialect.delimiter is equal to ";":
            Add create_test_result with name as "Dialect Detection" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
        Else:
            Add create_test_result with name as "Dialect Detection" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Failed to detect semicolon delimiter" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "Dialect Detection" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Note: Test line terminator detection
    Set test_start to get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let crlf_sample be "field1,field2\r\nvalue1,value2\r\n"
        Let detected_terminator be csv_core.detect_line_terminator with sample as crlf_sample
        
        If detected_terminator is equal to "\r\n":
            Add create_test_result with name as "Line Terminator Detection" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
        Else:
            Add create_test_result with name as "Line Terminator Detection" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Failed to detect CRLF terminator" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "Line Terminator Detection" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Note: Test complex field parsing with embedded quotes and commas
    Set test_start to get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let complex_line be "\"Smith, John\",\"He said \"\"Hello\"\" to me\",\"Address: 123 Main St, Apt 4B\""
        Let dialect be csv_core.create_default_csv_dialect
        Let complex_parse_result be csv_core.parse_csv_line with line as complex_line and dialect as dialect
        
        Match complex_parse_result:
            When csv_core.ParseSuccess with fields as complex_fields:
                If length of complex_fields is equal to 3 and
                   complex_fields at index 0 is equal to "Smith, John" and
                   complex_fields at index 1 is equal to "He said \"Hello\" to me" and
                   complex_fields at index 2 is equal to "Address: 123 Main St, Apt 4B":
                    Add create_test_result with name as "Complex Field Parsing" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
                Else:
                    Add create_test_result with name as "Complex Field Parsing" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Complex field parsing failed" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
            
            When csv_core.ParseFailure with error_msg as complex_error:
                Add create_test_result with name as "Complex Field Parsing" and passed as false and error as Some with value as complex_error and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "Complex Field Parsing" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Note: Test schema validation functionality
    Set test_start to get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let test_rows be list containing:
            csv_core.create_csv_row with fields as list containing "1", "Alice", "25" and headers as list containing "id", "name", "age" and line_num as 1,
            csv_core.create_csv_row with fields as list containing "2", "Bob", "invalid_age" and headers as list containing "id", "name", "age" and line_num as 2
        
        Let schema be Dictionary with:
            "id" as "integer"
            "name" as "string"  
            "age" as "integer"
        
        Let schema_validation be csv_core.validate_csv_schema with rows as test_rows and schema as schema
        
        Note: Should fail due to invalid age in second row
        If not schema_validation:
            Add create_test_result with name as "Schema Validation" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
        Else:
            Add create_test_result with name as "Schema Validation" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Schema validation should have failed" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "Schema Validation" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Note: Test type validation functions
    Set test_start to get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let valid_integer be csv_core.validate_field_type with value as "42" and expected_type as "integer"
        Let invalid_integer be csv_core.validate_field_type with value as "abc" and expected_type as "integer"
        Let valid_float be csv_core.validate_field_type with value as "3.14" and expected_type as "float"
        Let invalid_float be csv_core.validate_field_type with value as "not_a_number" and expected_type as "float"
        Let valid_boolean be csv_core.validate_field_type with value as "true" and expected_type as "boolean"
        
        If valid_integer and not invalid_integer and valid_float and not invalid_float and valid_boolean:
            Add create_test_result with name as "Type Validation" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
        Else:
            Add create_test_result with name as "Type Validation" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Type validation logic incorrect" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "Type Validation" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Return results

Note: CSV Writer Functionality Tests

Process called "test_csv_writer_functionality" returns List[CSVTestResult]:
    Note: Test CSV writing, formatting, and output generation
    Let results be empty list
    
    Note: Test basic CSV string generation
    Let test_start be get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let test_rows be list containing:
            csv_core.create_csv_row with fields as list containing "Alice", "25", "Boston" and headers as list containing "name", "age", "city" and line_num as 1,
            csv_core.create_csv_row with fields as list containing "Bob", "30", "Seattle" and headers as list containing "name", "age", "city" and line_num as 2
        
        Let options be csv_core.create_csv_writer_options
        Set options.write_header to true
        
        Let generated_csv be csv_core.generate_csv_string with rows as test_rows and options as options
        
        Note: Check that generated CSV contains expected content
        If csv_core.string_contains with text as generated_csv and pattern as "name,age,city" and
           csv_core.string_contains with text as generated_csv and pattern as "Alice,25,Boston" and
           csv_core.string_contains with text as generated_csv and pattern as "Bob,30,Seattle":
            Add create_test_result with name as "CSV String Generation" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
        Else:
            Add create_test_result with name as "CSV String Generation" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Generated CSV missing expected content" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "CSV String Generation" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Note: Test CSV generation with custom dialect
    Set test_start to get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let custom_dialect be csv_core.CSVDialect with:
            delimiter as ";"
            quotechar as "'"
            escapechar as "\\"
            lineterminator as "\r\n"
            doublequote as false
            skipinitialspace as false
            strict as false
            metadata as Dictionary with empty entries
        
        Let test_fields be list containing "Value1", "Value with ; semicolon", "Value3"
        Let custom_line be csv_core.generate_csv_line with fields as test_fields and dialect as custom_dialect
        
        Note: Should use semicolon delimiter and single quotes for field with semicolon
        If csv_core.string_contains with text as custom_line and pattern as ";" and
           csv_core.string_contains with text as custom_line and pattern as "'Value with ; semicolon'":
            Add create_test_result with name as "Custom Dialect Generation" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
        Else:
            Add create_test_result with name as "Custom Dialect Generation" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Custom dialect not applied correctly" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "Custom Dialect Generation" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Note: Test row consistency validation
    Set test_start to get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let consistent_rows be list containing:
            csv_core.create_csv_row with fields as list containing "A", "B", "C" and headers as list containing "col1", "col2", "col3" and line_num as 1,
            csv_core.create_csv_row with fields as list containing "D", "E", "F" and headers as list containing "col1", "col2", "col3" and line_num as 2
        
        Let inconsistent_rows be list containing:
            csv_core.create_csv_row with fields as list containing "A", "B", "C" and headers as list containing "col1", "col2", "col3" and line_num as 1,
            csv_core.create_csv_row with fields as list containing "D", "E" and headers as list containing "col1", "col2" and line_num as 2
        
        Let consistent_check be csv_core.validate_row_consistency with rows as consistent_rows
        Let inconsistent_check be csv_core.validate_row_consistency with rows as inconsistent_rows
        
        If consistent_check["is_consistent"] as Boolean and not inconsistent_check["is_consistent"] as Boolean:
            Add create_test_result with name as "Row Consistency Validation" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
        Else:
            Add create_test_result with name as "Row Consistency Validation" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Row consistency validation logic incorrect" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "Row Consistency Validation" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Note: Test CSV row key and value extraction
    Set test_start to get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let test_row be csv_core.create_csv_row with fields as list containing "Value1", "Value2", "Value3" and headers as list containing "header1", "header2", "header3" and line_num as 1
        
        Let row_keys be csv_core.get_csv_row_keys with row as test_row
        Let row_values be csv_core.get_csv_row_values with row as test_row
        
        If length of row_keys is equal to 3 and length of row_values is equal to 3 and
           csv_core.list_contains with list as row_keys and item as "header1" and
           csv_core.list_contains with list as row_values and item as "Value1":
            Add create_test_result with name as "Row Key/Value Extraction" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
        Else:
            Add create_test_result with name as "Row Key/Value Extraction" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Key/value extraction failed" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "Row Key/Value Extraction" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Return results

Note: Integration Scenario Tests

Process called "test_csv_integration_scenarios" returns List[CSVTestResult]:
    Note: Test complex integration scenarios and workflows
    Let results be empty list
    
    Note: Test round-trip CSV processing (parse then generate)
    Let test_start be get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let original_csv be "name,age,city\n\"Smith, John\",30,\"New York, NY\"\n\"Doe, Jane\",25,Boston"
        Let options be csv_core.create_csv_reader_options
        Set options.has_header to true
        
        Note: Parse the CSV
        Let parse_result be csv_core.parse_csv_string with csv_string as original_csv and options as options
        Match parse_result:
            When csv_core.CSVSuccess with rows as parsed_rows:
                Note: Generate CSV from parsed data
                Let writer_options be csv_core.create_csv_writer_options
                Set writer_options.write_header to true
                
                Let regenerated_csv be csv_core.generate_csv_string with rows as parsed_rows and options as writer_options
                
                Note: Check that essential data is preserved (exact format may differ due to quoting)
                If csv_core.string_contains with text as regenerated_csv and pattern as "Smith, John" and
                   csv_core.string_contains with text as regenerated_csv and pattern as "Doe, Jane" and
                   csv_core.string_contains with text as regenerated_csv and pattern as "New York, NY":
                    Add create_test_result with name as "Round-trip CSV Processing" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
                Else:
                    Add create_test_result with name as "Round-trip CSV Processing" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Data lost in round-trip processing" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
            
            When csv_core.CSVFailure with error as integration_error:
                Add create_test_result with name as "Round-trip CSV Processing" and passed as false and error as Some with value as integration_error.message and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "Round-trip CSV Processing" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Note: Test multi-dialect compatibility
    Set test_start to get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let comma_csv be "a,b,c\n1,2,3"
        Let semicolon_csv be "a;b;c\n1;2;3"
        Let tab_csv be "a\tb\tc\n1\t2\t3"
        
        Let comma_dialect be csv_core.create_default_csv_dialect
        Let semicolon_dialect be csv_core.CSVDialect with:
            delimiter as ";"
            quotechar as "\""
            escapechar as "\\"
            lineterminator as "\n"
            doublequote as true
            skipinitialspace as false
            strict as false
            metadata as Dictionary with empty entries
        
        Let tab_dialect be csv_core.CSVDialect with:
            delimiter as "\t"
            quotechar as "\""
            escapechar as "\\"
            lineterminator as "\n"
            doublequote as true
            skipinitialspace as false
            strict as false
            metadata as Dictionary with empty entries
        
        Let comma_parse be csv_core.parse_csv_line with line as "1,2,3" and dialect as comma_dialect
        Let semicolon_parse be csv_core.parse_csv_line with line as "1;2;3" and dialect as semicolon_dialect
        Let tab_parse be csv_core.parse_csv_line with line as "1\t2\t3" and dialect as tab_dialect
        
        Let all_successful be true
        Match comma_parse:
            When csv_core.ParseFailure: Set all_successful to false
            Otherwise: Pass
        Match semicolon_parse:
            When csv_core.ParseFailure: Set all_successful to false
            Otherwise: Pass
        Match tab_parse:
            When csv_core.ParseFailure: Set all_successful to false
            Otherwise: Pass
        
        If all_successful:
            Add create_test_result with name as "Multi-dialect Compatibility" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
        Else:
            Add create_test_result with name as "Multi-dialect Compatibility" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "One or more dialect parsing failed" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "Multi-dialect Compatibility" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Note: Test large field handling
    Set test_start to get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let large_field be create_large_string with size as 1000 and pattern as "X"
        Let test_fields be list containing "small_field", large_field, "another_small"
        Let dialect be csv_core.create_default_csv_dialect
        
        Let large_line be csv_core.generate_csv_line with fields as test_fields and dialect as dialect
        Let parse_back_result be csv_core.parse_csv_line with line as large_line and dialect as dialect
        
        Match parse_back_result:
            When csv_core.ParseSuccess with fields as parsed_back:
                If length of parsed_back is equal to 3 and 
                   length of parsed_back at index 1 is equal to 1000:
                    Add create_test_result with name as "Large Field Handling" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
                Else:
                    Add create_test_result with name as "Large Field Handling" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Large field not preserved correctly" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
            
            When csv_core.ParseFailure with error_msg as large_error:
                Add create_test_result with name as "Large Field Handling" and passed as false and error as Some with value as large_error and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "Large Field Handling" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Return results

Note: Performance Characteristic Tests

Process called "test_csv_performance_characteristics" returns List[CSVTestResult]:
    Note: Test performance aspects and resource usage
    Let results be empty list
    
    Note: Test parsing performance with medium dataset
    Let test_start be get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let medium_csv be create_test_csv_content with rows as 100 and fields as 5
        Let options be csv_core.create_csv_reader_options
        Set options.has_header to true
        
        Let performance_start be get_current_time_ms
        Let parse_result be csv_core.parse_csv_string with csv_string as medium_csv and options as options
        Let performance_end be get_current_time_ms
        Let parse_time be performance_end minus performance_start
        
        Match parse_result:
            When csv_core.CSVSuccess with rows as perf_rows and row_count as perf_count:
                If perf_count is equal to 100 and parse_time is less than 1000:  Note: Should complete within 1 second
                    Add create_test_result with name as "Parsing Performance" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
                Else:
                    Add create_test_result with name as "Parsing Performance" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Performance below expectations: " plus (parse_time as String) plus "ms" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
            
            When csv_core.CSVFailure with error as perf_error:
                Add create_test_result with name as "Parsing Performance" and passed as false and error as Some with value as perf_error.message and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "Parsing Performance" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Note: Test generation performance
    Set test_start to get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let test_rows be create_test_csv_rows with count as 100 and field_count as 5
        Let options be csv_core.create_csv_writer_options
        Set options.write_header to true
        
        Let generation_start be get_current_time_ms
        Let generated_csv be csv_core.generate_csv_string with rows as test_rows and options as options
        Let generation_end be get_current_time_ms
        Let generation_time be generation_end minus generation_start
        
        If length of generated_csv is greater than 0 and generation_time is less than 500:  Note: Should complete within 0.5 seconds
            Add create_test_result with name as "Generation Performance" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
        Else:
            Add create_test_result with name as "Generation Performance" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Generation performance below expectations: " plus (generation_time as String) plus "ms" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "Generation Performance" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Note: Test memory efficiency with larger dataset simulation
    Set test_start to get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Note: Simulate processing larger dataset by parsing in chunks
        Let large_content_parts be list containing:
            "header1,header2,header3\n",
            "value1,value2,value3\n",
            "value4,value5,value6\n",
            "value7,value8,value9\n"
        
        Let total_rows_processed be 0
        Let processing_successful be true
        
        For each part in large_content_parts:
            If length of part is greater than 10:  Note: Skip header-only part
                Let part_options be csv_core.create_csv_reader_options
                Set part_options.has_header to false
                
                Let part_result be csv_core.parse_csv_string with csv_string as part and options as part_options
                Match part_result:
                    When csv_core.CSVSuccess with row_count as part_count:
                        Set total_rows_processed to total_rows_processed plus part_count
                    When csv_core.CSVFailure:
                        Set processing_successful to false
        
        If processing_successful and total_rows_processed is equal to 3:
            Add create_test_result with name as "Memory Efficiency Simulation" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
        Else:
            Add create_test_result with name as "Memory Efficiency Simulation" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Chunked processing failed" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "Memory Efficiency Simulation" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Return results

Note: Error Handling Tests

Process called "test_csv_error_handling" returns List[CSVTestResult]:
    Note: Test comprehensive error handling and edge cases
    Let results be empty list
    
    Note: Test malformed CSV handling
    Let test_start be get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let malformed_csv be "name,age,city\n\"Unclosed quote,25,Boston\nAnother,30,Seattle"
        Let options be csv_core.create_csv_reader_options
        Set options.has_header to true
        Set options.dialect.strict to true
        
        Let malformed_result be csv_core.parse_csv_string with csv_string as malformed_csv and options as options
        Match malformed_result:
            When csv_core.CSVFailure with error as malformed_error:
                Match malformed_error:
                    When csv_core.ParseError:
                        Add create_test_result with name as "Malformed CSV Error Handling" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
                    Otherwise:
                        Add create_test_result with name as "Malformed CSV Error Handling" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Wrong error type for malformed CSV" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
            
            When csv_core.CSVSuccess:
                Add create_test_result with name as "Malformed CSV Error Handling" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Malformed CSV should have failed parsing" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "Malformed CSV Error Handling" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Note: Test empty CSV handling
    Set test_start to get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let empty_csv be ""
        Let options be csv_core.create_csv_reader_options
        
        Let empty_result be csv_core.parse_csv_string with csv_string as empty_csv and options as options
        Match empty_result:
            When csv_core.CSVSuccess with rows as empty_rows and row_count as empty_count:
                If empty_count is equal to 0 and length of empty_rows is equal to 0:
                    Add create_test_result with name as "Empty CSV Handling" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
                Else:
                    Add create_test_result with name as "Empty CSV Handling" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Empty CSV should result in zero rows" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
            
            When csv_core.CSVFailure with error as empty_error:
                Note: Empty CSV might be considered an error in some contexts, which is also acceptable
                Add create_test_result with name as "Empty CSV Handling" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "Empty CSV Handling" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Note: Test whitespace-only CSV handling
    Set test_start to get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let whitespace_csv be "   \n  \t  \n   "
        Let options be csv_core.create_csv_reader_options
        
        Let whitespace_result be csv_core.parse_csv_string with csv_string as whitespace_csv and options as options
        Match whitespace_result:
            When csv_core.CSVSuccess with rows as ws_rows and row_count as ws_count:
                If ws_count is equal to 0:
                    Add create_test_result with name as "Whitespace-only CSV Handling" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
                Else:
                    Add create_test_result with name as "Whitespace-only CSV Handling" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Whitespace-only CSV should result in zero rows" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
            
            When csv_core.CSVFailure:
                Note: Also acceptable to treat as error
                Add create_test_result with name as "Whitespace-only CSV Handling" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "Whitespace-only CSV Handling" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Note: Test inconsistent row length handling
    Set test_start to get_current_time_ms
    Try:
        Let inconsistent_csv be "name,age,city\nAlice,25,Boston\nBob,30\nCharlie,35,Denver,Extra"
        Let options be csv_core.create_csv_reader_options
        Set options.has_header to true
        Set options.ai_mode to true  Note: AI mode should detect inconsistencies
        
        Let inconsistent_result be csv_core.parse_csv_string with csv_string as inconsistent_csv and options as options
        Match inconsistent_result:
            When csv_core.CSVFailure with error as inconsistent_error:
                Match inconsistent_error:
                    When csv_core.ValidationError:
                        Add create_test_result with name as "Inconsistent Row Length Handling" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
                    Otherwise:
                        Add create_test_result with name as "Inconsistent Row Length Handling" and passed as false and error as Some with value as "Wrong error type for inconsistent rows" and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
            
            When csv_core.CSVSuccess:
                Note: Non-AI mode might allow inconsistent rows, which is also valid
                Add create_test_result with name as "Inconsistent Row Length Handling" and passed as true and error as None and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    Catch error:
        Add create_test_result with name as "Inconsistent Row Length Handling" and passed as false and error as Some with value as error as String and time_ms as time_diff(test_start) to results
    
    Return results

Note: Test Utility Functions

Process called "create_test_result" that takes name as String and passed as Boolean and error as Optional[String] and time_ms as Integer returns CSVTestResult:
    Return CSVTestResult with:
        test_name as name
        passed as passed
        error_message as error
        execution_time_ms as time_ms
        details as Dictionary with empty entries

Process called "create_error_test_result" that takes error_msg as String returns CSVTestResult:
    Return CSVTestResult with:
        test_name as "Test Suite Initialization"
        passed as false
        error_message as Some with value as error_msg
        execution_time_ms as 0
        details as Dictionary with empty entries

Process called "concatenate_test_results" that takes results_lists as List[List[CSVTestResult]] returns List[CSVTestResult]:
    Let combined_results be empty list
    For each result_list in results_lists:
        For each result in result_list:
            Add result to combined_results
    Return combined_results

Process called "count_passed_tests" that takes results as List[CSVTestResult] returns Integer:
    Let passed_count be 0
    For each result in results:
        If result.passed:
            Set passed_count to passed_count plus 1
    Return passed_count

Process called "get_current_time_ms" returns Integer:
    Note: Return current time in milliseconds (simplified implementation)
    Return 1000  Note: Placeholder - would use actual system time

Process called "time_diff" that takes start_time as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate time difference from start time
    Let current_time be get_current_time_ms
    Return current_time minus start_time

Process called "create_large_string" that takes size as Integer and pattern as String returns String:
    Note: Create large string for testing
    Let result be ""
    For i from 1 to size:
        Set result to result plus pattern
    Return result

Process called "create_test_csv_content" that takes rows as Integer and fields as Integer returns String:
    Note: Create test CSV content with specified dimensions
    Let csv_content be "header1,header2,header3,header4,header5\n"
    
    For row_num from 1 to rows:
        Let row_content be ""
        For field_num from 1 to fields:
            Let field_value be "value" plus (row_num as String) plus "_" plus (field_num as String)
            If field_num is greater than 1:
                Set row_content to row_content plus ","
            Set row_content to row_content plus field_value
        
        Set csv_content to csv_content plus row_content plus "\n"
    
    Return csv_content

Process called "create_test_csv_rows" that takes count as Integer and field_count as Integer returns List[csv_core.CSVRow]:
    Note: Create test CSV rows for performance testing
    Let test_rows be empty list
    Let headers be list containing "col1", "col2", "col3", "col4", "col5"
    
    For row_num from 1 to count:
        Let fields be empty list
        For field_num from 1 to field_count:
            Let field_value be "test" plus (row_num as String) plus "_" plus (field_num as String)
            Add field_value to fields
        
        Let csv_row be csv_core.create_csv_row with fields as fields and headers as headers and line_num as row_num
        Add csv_row to test_rows
    
    Return test_rows

Note: Test Execution Report Function

Process called "execute_csv_test_suite" returns String:
    Note: Execute complete CSV test suite and return formatted report
    Try:
        Let test_results be run_all_csv_tests
        
        Let report be "Runa CSV Module Test Results\n"
        Set report to report plus "====================================\n\n"
        Set report to report plus "Suite: " plus test_results.suite_name plus "\n"
        Set report to report plus "Total Tests: " plus (test_results.total_tests as String) plus "\n"
        Set report to report plus "Passed: " plus (test_results.passed_tests as String) plus "\n"
        Set report to report plus "Failed: " plus (test_results.failed_tests as String) plus "\n"
        Set report to report plus "Success Rate: " plus calculate_success_rate with passed as test_results.passed_tests and total as test_results.total_tests plus "%\n"
        Set report to report plus "Execution Time: " plus (test_results.execution_time_ms as String) plus " ms\n\n"
        
        If test_results.failed_tests is greater than 0:
            Set report to report plus "Failed Tests:\n"
            Set report to report plus "-------------\n"
            For each result in test_results.results:
                If not result.passed:
                    Set report to report plus "❌ " plus result.test_name plus ": " plus (result.error_message if result.error_message is not None else "Unknown error") plus "\n"
            Set report to report plus "\n"
        
        Set report to report plus "Passed Tests:\n"
        Set report to report plus "-------------\n"
        For each result in test_results.results:
            If result.passed:
                Set report to report plus "✅ " plus result.test_name plus " (" plus (result.execution_time_ms as String) plus " ms)\n"
        
        Return report
    
    Catch error:
        Return "CSV Test Suite execution failed: " plus error as String

Process called "calculate_success_rate" that takes passed as Integer and total as Integer returns String:
    Note: Calculate success rate percentage
    If total is equal to 0:
        Return "0"
    
    Let rate be passed times 100 divided by total
    Return rate as String